examples.en: He silently drank down his beer.
She silently mouthed the words 'Good luck'.
He didn't shout, he just glared at me silently.
The cat came padding silently back to its home.
The passengers were either asleep or sitting silently, traumatized by the heat.
She sat silently, flinging the odd word into the conversation from time to time.
He sat silently by the bed.
He cried silently while the song played.
The children descended the staircase silently.
She sat in the car, silently fuming about what he'd said.
Silently she closed the door. Just then she heard a noise.
We went along silently on tiptoe so as not to disturb anyone.
